  "articleSummary": "The article argues that \"generative UI\" is not a single technology but a layered stack—product shell, UI composition model, runtime/transport, and agent backend—and that conflating these layers leads to confusion. It frames chat as \"training wheels\" and presents a control spectrum from safe tool-to-component rendering to open-ended generated HTML, urging developers to choose the minimal freedom needed. Key technologies discussed include AG-UI, A2UI, json-render, CopilotKit, and MCP Apps, each serving distinct layers. The tone is analytical and educational, aimed at developers and architects navigating the emerging LLM UI ecosystem, using metaphors like \"soup\" for confusion and \"map\" for the layered framework.",
